  "text": "Transit Gateway is OSS's managed service for connecting VPCs, VPNs, and on-premises networks. Unlike VPC peering, Transit Gateway is transitive. You connect multiple VPCs to a central hub, and they can all communicate with each other. This creates a hub-and-spoke topology. Transit Gateway supports up to 5,000 attachments and can span multiple regions. It's ideal for complex architectures with many VPCs or when you need centralized routing and Transit Gateway uses route tables to comprone which attachment.",
